{"text": "Hello and welcome to the Self-Gravity Practice of our meditation program. That is strongly related to the sense of self and developing the internal presence. For this center of gravity plays as a crucial gateway to building this internal self-presence. Identify your precise location exactly where you are. Let us trigger the practice by exhalation in a vertical, top-down fashion. Exhaled from your nose, from your chest, finish with exhaling from the belly and emptying your body of air. Exhaled from the nose, from the chest, pull the belly in to push out air, pull it in a little more, imp to yourself completely of air, then allow your body to breathing naturally, shallow or deep as it wishes. Again, attention on the exhale from the nose, from the nose, from chest, from the belly, pull the lower belly in, push out the air, let your body become empty of air. It can then easily inhale the air into your empty body. Continue exhaling downward from the top, from your chest, from the belly. No need to focus on inhaling but the body breathing by itself, again from the nose, from chest, from the belly. Again, a vertical exhale, pull the belly in to push out the air. Again, focus only on exhale, top-down, the vertical exhale. Next exhale, bring your attention towards your chest area. Exhale all the way down, from next exhale, bring your mind lower to the abdominal area. Again, exhale from the belly, bring your mind lower to the waist, lower to the belly. Exhale again, from the top, from the chest, from the belly. Reach the point in your lower belly, in the center, deep in the belly. Use the exhalation to help you reach the point of gravity. Again, reach the center of gravity. Pull the belly in to push out the air and anchor in the center of gravity. Use your exhale to help you anchor in the point of gravity. Deep in the belly. Reach the center of gravity. If a thought arises, shift your mind from thinking to center. Pull the belly back to center. Now, I deserve your center of gravity. Let go of any breathing focus. Just go to the center of gravity. Observe the center of gravity. From thought to center. To the center. Back to center. You may now raise your attention from the center upward. Towards the abdominal area. Gently and slowly lifting up towards the chest. To the throat. Rising up to the center of the head. Come out through the ears and hear every sound. The sound of anything you can hear. To the center. And slowly come back to the center of the head. Lower to the throat. To the chest. Down to the abdomen. Down towards the center of gravity. The mind connecting to the center of gravity. Establishing the vertical link from the center of gravity. Through the chest and throat to the center of head. The central link from the lower center to the upper center. The vertical inner presence. The vertical presence. From the belly to the head. From point of gravity to the chest. To the center of head. Stay in this inner presence. The vertical internal presence. From point of gravity to the center of gravity. The inner vertical presence. The home within. From point of gravity to the center of gravity. From lower center to the middle to the upper center. The vertical connection. The vertical self presence. From point of gravity to the center of gravity. The internal presence. From point of gravity to the center of gravity. Cover your eyes with your palms. Cover your ears and hear yourself. Bring the palms in front of your eyes. Open your eyes on your palms. The first thing you see is yourself. The second thing you see is yourself.", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 16.28, "end": 29.82, "text": " Hello and welcome to the Self-Gravity Practice of our meditation program.", "tokens": [50364, 2425, 293, 2928, 281, 264, 16348, 12, 38, 13404, 507, 27904, 295, 527, 12537, 1461, 13, 51862], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.4031349182128906, "compression_ratio": 0.9864864864864865, "no_speech_prob": 0.16552378237247467, "words": 